cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to summarize legal documents. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves techniques such as unsupervised extractive summarization, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves manual verification of summaries, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to extract relevant information from legal documents, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper also involves cybersecurity and privacy concerns related to legal documents, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
